cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.AI 

This paper is primarily focused on learning structured dynamical systems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also uses sparse optimization techniques, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of random sampling and theoretical guarantees on recovery rates suggests a numerical analysis (cs.NA) component to the paper. Finally, the paper deals with datasets generated by various differential equations, which falls under the category of dynamical systems (cs.DS).
